{"0":"All 65 papers accounted for: 65 in rename mapping, 65 classified across 6 categories, and 3 caption-related papers with their Table 2 extracted. Everything is complete.\n\nHere's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Tasks Completed\n\n### 1. Rename Mapping (65 papers)\nAll 65 PDFs have been:\n- Title extracted from PDF metadata/text (using font-size analysis + fallbacks)\n- Renamed with spaces→`_` and `/`→`_`\n- Copied to `/tmp_workspace/results/papers/` (flat structure)\n- Full mapping table written to `paper_digest.md`\n\n### 2. Classification (65 papers total)\n| Category | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Multimodal / Vision-Language Models | 16 |\n| Medical Image Analysis | 6 |\n| Image / Video Generation & Editing | 16 |\n| Autonomous Driving / Robotics / Embodied AI | 4 |\n| 3D Vision / Reconstruction / Gaussian Splatting | 7 |\n| Others | 16 |\n\n### 3. Caption-Related Papers & Table 2 Extraction\nFound **3 papers** with strong image captioning focus **and** a Table 2:\n\n1. **CapRL: Stimulating Dense Image Caption Capabilities via Reinforcement Learning** — Table 2 shows ablation on image sources (InfoVQA, DocVQA, ChartQA, etc. benchmarks across different pretraining datasets)\n\n2. **Asymmetric Idiosyncrasies in Multimodal Models** — Table 2 shows top distinctive TF-IDF phrases per captioning model (Claude, Gemini, GPT-4o, Qwen3-VL)\n\n3. **Scale Can't Overcome Pragmatics: The Impact of Reporting Bias on Vision-Language Reasoning** — Table 2 shows benchmark results across 20 VLMs on spatial/negation/counting/temporal reasoning\n\n*(Note: \"Cytoarchitecture in Words\" is also caption-related but only has 1 table in the paper)*","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.1","hostname":"8e03d3573340","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-06-27T14:51:03.150Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975:46","fileName":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsys